## Scope and Rules of Engagement

Every professional engagement begins with a document defining:

- **In scope** — what IP ranges, domains, and systems you are permitted to test
- **Out of scope** — what you must not touch, often production databases or third-party services
- **Testing window** — when you are permitted to test
- **Emergency contact** — who to call if you accidentally cause an outage or find something critical
- **Reporting requirements** — format and deadline

Staying within scope is not optional. Testing systems outside scope — even accidentally — can void your legal protection. If during a test you discover systems appear connected to out-of-scope infrastructure, stop, document it, and notify your contact.

